Photography View;
A COLOR SHOW OUT OF FOCUS;
WASHINGTON, D.C.  Color photography is so prevalent today that it is hard to imagine a time when it did not exist. The amateur snapshooter hardly uses anything else, it dominates the mass media, it has important uses in science and technology, and it has even, in the past decade, established itself in the art gallery and museum.
